  • Method Details

    • getUnusedScoringOptions

      java.util.List<IScoringOption> getUnusedScoringOptions()
      Returns a list of all scoring options the person has not used, even if they are not satisfied by current dice.

    • getUnusedScoringOptionsSatisfiedByCurrentDice

      java.util.List<IScoringOption> getUnusedScoringOptionsSatisfiedByCurrentDice()
      Returns:
      A list of scoring options that are satisfied by the current dice and which have not already used

    • getUsedScoringOptions

      java.util.List<IScoringOption> getUsedScoringOptions()
      Returns all the scoring options on this score card for which a score has been recorded. This is used to test that the player has registered a score for each round.

    • getHighestScoringOption

      IScoringOption getHighestScoringOption()
      Returns the available scoring option that has the highest score given the current dice values.

    • getTotalScore

      int getTotalScore()
      Returns the total score for each used scoring option on this score card, including the optional bonus on the upper section.

    • getUpperScoreWithoutBonus

      int getUpperScoreWithoutBonus()
      Returns the upper score without the bonus that applies when the upper score is above 63.

    • getBonus

      int getBonus()
      Returns the value of the bonus applied to the upper score if upper score is above 63. The bonus is 35.
      Returns:
      35 if the upper score is 63 or greater, and zero otherwise

    • getLowerScore

      int getLowerScore()
      Gets the score for the 'lower' scoring options.
